  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Users can reserve blocks of time for customers to come in and spend time with an assigned user. You can also specify whether this appointment is meant for a Repair ticket, Sales ticket, or a Trade-in ticket. If a customer decides they no longer need their reservation, users can cancel the appointment from the Appointment List.\u00a0</p><h3 id=\"Appointments:CancelinganAppointment-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934491696/Appointments\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934491696\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Appointments Overview</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933246822/Appointments+General+Settings\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933246822\" data-linked-resource-version=\"16\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Appointments: General Settings</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934917649/Appointments+Scheduling+an+Appointment\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934917649\" data-linked-resource-version=\"5\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Appointments: Scheduling an Appointment</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934852150/Appointments+Changing+an+Appointment\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934852150\" data-linked-resource-version=\"8\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Appointments: Changing an Appointment</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"680\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934491709/Instructional%20-%200091cd.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"Appointments:CancelinganAppointment-LocatingtheAppointmentList\">Locating the Appointment List</h2><p>To find your Appointment List, use the Navigation Bar at the top of RepairQ to go to <strong>Opportunities</strong> \u2192 <strong>Appointments</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934491709/Cancel%20Appointment%201.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"Appointments:CancelinganAppointment-ViewingSetAppointments\">Viewing Set Appointments</h2><p>After an appointment is set, it will appear on the Appointments List View page.\u00a0</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934491709/Cancel%20Appointment%202.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>The Appointments List View page allows users to search for appointments by Name, Device, Request Type, and more. For more on how list views and searching work, please see our article, <a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://repairq.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/360036175453-Custom-List-Views-Filters-and-Columns\" rel=\"nofollow\">Custom List Views, Filters, and Columns</a>.</p><p>You can view scheduled appointments by\u00a0<strong>List</strong>,\u00a0<strong>Day</strong>,\u00a0<strong>Week</strong>, or\u00a0<strong>Month</strong>. In each view, you will notice a left and right arrow that allow you to cycle between the unit of time.\u00a0There is also a\u00a0<strong>today</strong> button, which when viewing the\u00a0<strong>Day</strong> style will bring you back to the current date.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934491709/Cancel%20Appointment%203.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"Appointments:CancelinganAppointment-CancelinganAppointment\">Canceling an Appointment</h2><p>We'll walk you through a quick example using <strong>Bob Roberts'</strong> name as a keyword to narrow results to find their <strong>November 28th</strong> appointment and cancel it.\u00a0</p><p /><p>1. From the Appointments List View filter, select <strong>+Keyword</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934491709/Cancel%20Appointment%209.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>2. Enter your keyword (<strong>Bob Roberts</strong>), then select <strong>Apply</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934491709/Cancel%20Appointment%2010.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>3. From the narrowed results, scroll through to find the appointment you would like to cancel and click the <strong>Options Menu</strong> below the <strong>Action\u00a0</strong>column.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934491709/Cancel%20Appointment%2011.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"226\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934491709/Cancel%20Appointment%2012.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>4. From the\u00a0<strong>Options Menu</strong>, select\u00a0<strong>Cancel</strong>. When you are finished, the list view will refresh, and the appointment will be canceled and removed from the appointment list.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934491709/Cancel%20Appointment%2013.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p><strong>Note</strong>: You can view canceled appointments by selecting the filter <strong>Status - Canceled</strong>.</p><p /><p /><p>START 1.18.X</p>",
